U.S. Envoy Urges New Steps to Carry Forward Kosovo Peace
BELGRADE , November 14 ( Xinhua ) -- U.S. envoy Christopher Hill said Saturday that the time has arrived to work out a new formula to carry forward the peace process in Kosovo , the Tanjug news agency reported .
" I think we are coming to the point where we start thinking about what this agreement is going to look like , get all the details down , " he said in Pristina , capital of Kosovo , after a meeting with Ibrahim Rugova , leader of Kosovo 's ethnic Albanian majority .
Describing the discussion as " very good " , Hill said they agreed in general on a timetable for a proposed new peace accord to solve the Kosovo crisis .
Hill also briefed Rugova on his talks held here Friday with Milan Milutinovic , president of Republic of Serbia , who received a copy of the draft new accord .
According to the U.S. envoy , Milutinovic said he would leave for Pristina next week to invite ethnic Albanian leaders to peace talks .
Hill expressed the hope that the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe ( OSCE ) verification mission would help implement the agreement reached between Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic and U.S. envoy Richard Holbrooke .
